Use Case: ArrangeShips 
Scope: BattleShip
Primary Actor: User
Intention: Move ships to a position pleasing the User in preparation for the game.
Level: Subfunction
Multiplicity: One user moves one set of ships.
Main Success Scenario:
  1. System displays all the ships the User can place.
  2. User selects a ship and clicks on the gamemap where it should go.
  3. System verifies the position is valid.
  4. System moves the ship to the indicated position and displays
     this to the User.
  5. System removes the ship from the list of ships to be placed.
     If ships remain, Use Case continues at step 2.
Extensions:
  4a. System determines the position to be invalid.
      Use Case continues at step 2.
